node.text:
Extreme AB Workout💀 We can post your photos and videos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures.

4 Unique Exercises To Sculpt a Strong Core🖤Swipe and Try!

ALL you need for this workout is a BENCH and Weight to get a Insane core workout

As you guys know I love to get creative with my core workouts! It’s so easy to get stuck into the routine of doing crunches and sit-ups! If you want to build a strong core then you must train your Abs like every other muscle...change up your routine and challenge yourself

Adding in things like a box, kettlebell, decline bench to your ab routine is a great way to progressing overload your abs and build a stronger, sculpted core

The Details🤘🏼Perform each exercise back to back circuit style with minimal to no rest in between exercises! After you complete a round rest for 1 to 2 minutes and repeat for 3 to 4

1️⃣ Elevated Oblique Crunches x20
2️⃣ Plate Halos x20
3️⃣ Iso Hold With Core Rotation x20
4️⃣ Decline Single Leg Crunch Variation x20
5️⃣ Decline scissor Kicks x20 📹 @elizabethaylorfitness

node.text:
Kneeling Squat 🍑 We can share your content in our page, check the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory to follow the process. 

The kneeling squat maximizes glute activation.
The target muscles are the gluteus maximus and quadriceps femoris (red)

Maintaining a neutral lumbar spine.
The fully flexed spine is associated with strained posterior passive tissues and high shearing forces on the lumbar spine. (Mc Gill, Low Back Disorders, 2007)

The movement is through the hip joint. Keep your back straight‼️
.
Tell your trainee to "squeeze the buttocks", not by creating hip extension.
Then, once the activation has been mastered, the trainee begins extending the torso through the hip joint.

It is best to perform this exercise with some padding on the floor, so you won’t harm your knees.

📽 @muscleandmotion

Bodyweight Only Upper Body 💪 Get your photos/videos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting runningterritory.com/feature 👉🏼the link is in our bio: @RunningTerritory. 

The best part about bodyweight only workouts is the ability to do them anywhere, anytime. A little change of scenery does the body and mind good!

3 Rounds x 10 Reps Each. 📹 @sweatysorrentino

INNER THIGHS BAABY 🍗 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our page, use the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory

Swipe left & Save! Please leave a LIKE and save the video for later thank you so so much for the love and support

perfect comes in different shapes ⭐️ that’s what makes us unique! I get many requests on “how to get rid of inner thighs”.. try to see that this makes YOUR body unique.
you know I’m here for y’all and I wanna provide you with as much content as possible. you absolutely can train your inner thighs but remember that we can’t spot reduce fat queens. training & nutrition goes hand in hand!

give these a try and let me know what you think. remember, you are beautiful.

METHOD:

1️⃣ sumo squat variation // 3set x 10reps each leg
2️⃣ side lunge variation // 3set x 10reps each leg
3️⃣ lying hand to toe taps // 3set x 10reps each leg
4️⃣ crossovers to stretch out // 3set x 15-20reps 📹 @hannaoeberg

node.text:
Avoiding overstriding 🦵We can post your photos and videos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures. 

Avoiding overstriding is a super easy way to boost your performance and at the same time decrease the force/impact on your body and limit the risk of injuries. Overstriding is a common running mistake that occurs when you are making ground contact too far in front of your center of mass. To help you avoiding overstriding here are some tips and tricks:

1️⃣ Use your phone for filming you from the side (best is to use the slow-mo function) and take a look at where your foot is landing in relation to your body

2️⃣ a higher cadence (steps/minute) lowers the possibility for overstriding so try running the same speed but with faster (shorter) steps (check out my playlist for the right beats per minute, link on bio :)

3️⃣ Include running uphill (4-5% incline) to your training as it is almost impossible to have overstriding when running uphill as you are forced into a certain running posture. By that you will get the feeling of making ground contact below your hips/center of mass. You can also do these uphill runs as intervals of running uphill for a longer time is hard 🤙

📽 @fabi_horni_tri
🎶 K-391, Alan Walker, Ahrix - End of Time
